INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(93, 1, '2013-11-18 08:10:58', '2013-11-18 08:10:58', 'On the date of 1st August 2013,  Acme Firefox and AOSC [Acme Open Source Community]  jointly organized and event named Acme Mozilla Orientation. The event was said to be started from 10:00 AM  but a huge traffic jam at Banasthali Chowk it was half hour delayed and it was started from 10:30 AM.\r\n\r\nThe five member of Mozilla Nepal team entered the college:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Avash Mulmi</li>\r\n	<li>Prashish Rajbhandari</li>\r\n	<li>Avinash Kundaliya</li>\r\n	<li>Bansaj Pradhan</li>\r\n	<li>Nirmal Khanal</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAvash Mulmi started the event with their introduction one by one and then all the event participant also gave their introduction.<img alt="Avash Mulmi Starting the Event" src="https://fbcdn-sphotos-b-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-ash4/1004497_559822487411240_362742799_n.jpg" /> With the participant of 25 student and our HOD sir the event  get started and at the starting of the event Prashish Rajbhandari and  Avinash Kundaliya ask us a question " What is Open Source? " we all get quiet for while because we don''t know the right and complete answer of the question. But after the silence of while one of the student and member of AOSC "Nikesh Balami" stood up and gives an answer but the answer given by him wasn''t complete So, both brother teach us the right definition of Open Source.\r\n\r\nAfter a little talk of Mozilla and Mozilla Nepal Prashish Rajbhandari and Avash Mulmi told use how we can contribute on Mozilla. Avash  Mulmi told us about different kinds of involvement process :\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Helping Users</li>\r\n	<li>Testing and Quality Assurance</li>\r\n	<li>Coding</li>\r\n	<li>Marketing  and Evangelism</li>\r\n	<li>Localization</li>\r\n	<li>Add-ons</li>\r\n	<li>Visual Design</li>\r\n	<li>Developer Documentation</li>\r\n	<li>Accessibility</li>\r\n	<li>System Administration</li>\r\n	<li>User Research</li>\r\n	<li>Education</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAvinash Kundaliya gave us the presentation about Firefox OS. He told us how the Firefox OS is made and Gave us a small demo of the coding. Firefox OS is made up of HTML, CSS and JS . Avinash Kundaliya teach us all the working principle of that OS and He also teach us how to use Firefox OS on Simulator.<img alt="Avinash bro Giving the Firefox OS presentation" src="https://fbcdn-sphotos-h-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-ash4/p206x206/1002504_559822457411243_433956189_n.jpg" />\r\n\r\nThen again  Bansaj Pradhan give a small demo of Localization. He teach us how it work and how to contribute on it. Alot of student was interested on this topics and want to work on it.<img alt="Demo Presentation" src="https://fbcdn-sphotos-e-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-prn1/24280_559822320744590_2105664924_n.jpg" />\r\n\r\nAt last Nikesh Balami a member of Acme Open Source Community takes the feedback of all student and ask them wheather they are interested to do next Workshop of Web Maker or not. All the student gave the Positive answer and then he ask the student in which field they want to contribute and with the collection of all answer  and positive Feedback the event ends.<img alt="Nikesh Balami asking Feedback" src="https://fbcdn-sphotos-h-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-prn1/60093_559824560744366_1938206990_n.jpg" />\r\n\r\nAt last a group photo was taken:<img alt="Group Photo" src="https://fbcdn-sphotos-f-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-ash4/1003336_559824934077662_1395025935_n.jpg" />', 'Acme Mozilla Orentation', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'acme-mozilla-orentation', '', '', '2014-02-24 05:58:01', '2014-02-24 05:58:01', '', 0, 'http://www.neekes.com.np/?p=93', 0, 'post', '', 1);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(7, 1, '2014-05-13 06:17:00', '2014-05-13 06:17:00', '<a href="http://www.neekes.com.np/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/555712_346953785364779_488083783_n.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-207" alt="555712_346953785364779_488083783_n" src="http://www.neekes.com.np/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/555712_346953785364779_488083783_n-200x300.jpg" width="200" height="300" /></a>\n\n<style type="text/css"><!--\np { margin-bottom: 0.1in; line-height: 120%; }\n--></style>\n<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">         Strong Supporter of Free and Open Source Software (FOSS), Open Education, Open Web, Open GLAM, Open Content, Open Data etc. and Working with different Open Communities of Nepal Since 2012 to bring some Technology Revolution in Nepal cuz I believe only Technology can make some big Impact. I have done Diploma in Computer Engineering from Acme Engineering College, Banasthali Chowk, Kathmandu, Nepal. </span></p>\n<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">I am one Computer Geek &amp; Geek''s always Love Open Source “Rocking Open Source” </span></p>\n<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">My Involvement with Different Communities</span></p>\n<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">1) <strong>Open Knowledge Foundation Network Nepal</strong></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">Data Wrangler in <a href="http://np.okfn.org/2013/07/24/kathmandu-metropolitan-in-city-spending-data-party/"><span style="color: #0000ff;">Kathmandu Metropolitan City Spending Data Party</span> </a></span></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">Data Wrangler in <a href="http://np.okfn.org/2013/09/29/mini-spending-party-in-kathmandu-nepal-budget-201314/"><span style="color: #0000ff;">Mini Spending Party</span> </a></span></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li><span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">Data Visualization of <a hr