INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(45, 1, '2013-11-08 03:57:19', '2013-11-08 03:57:19', '<a href="http://neekes.com.np/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Screenshot-from-2013-10-31-125424.png"><img alt="Screenshot from 2013-10-31 12:54:24" src="http://neekes.com.np/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Screenshot-from-2013-10-31-125424-300x176.png" width="800" height="376" /></a><strong>Who we are?</strong>\r\n\r\nFirefox Student Ambassadors are individuals from around the world who are passionate about Mozilla and want to spread the word about the many benefits of Firefox and our other products – especially Firefox OS !\r\n\r\nThey act as campus guides for people who want to contribute to Mozilla and function as leaders for campaigns and projects that help build a brighter future for the Web globally.\r\n\r\n<strong>How to sign up?</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you''re 18 or older and currently associated with an institution of higher education (students, professors and administrators are all welcome!), please visit our wiki page to find our how you can become a Firefox Student Ambassador:\r\n<a href="http://wiki.mozilla.org/StudentAmbassadors/Join" target="_blank">wiki.mozilla.org/StudentAmbassadors/Join</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Student Ambassador/Recognition:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Recognition:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Level 1</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Firefox Student Ambassador Open Badge</strong>\r\n\r\nAn open badge will be awarded to any Student Ambassador who completes the following tasks:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Officially registers for the program</li>\r\n	<li>Becomes familiar with Mozilla (completes <a href="https://wiki.mozilla.org/StudentAmbassadors/Activities/Startup_Guide">Step 1</a> of the first 5 steps that an Ambassador should do)</li>\r\n	<li>Does a Facebook/Twitter/Google+ post about the program using the hash-tags (#firefox #students #mozilla) and provides a link to the <a href="http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/contribute/universityambassadors/">registration form</a></li>\r\n	<li>Creates or joins a Firefox Club (please first join a Firefox Club if there is already one located at your school!)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYou can request an open badge <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/10IsyspUmaixL14IO-fUbuGByHX08-Rgdg5w5ShcEYvw/viewform">here</a>. Requests made for an open badge will be evaluated twice a month - <b>the first badges will be emailed out on November 11th.</b>\r\n\r\n<strong>Level 2</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Certificate of Identification</strong>\r\n\r\nA Certificate of identification as a Firefox Student Ambassador is available to each Ambassador who <b>has already been awarded their open badge</b> and completes one of the following actions:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Makes a thimble or popcorn video about their favorite Mozilla project</li>\r\n	<li>Writes a blog post about their experience in the program</li>\r\n	<li>Hosts a Firefox Club event on their campus (and posts a summary on their Club''s wiki page)</li>\r\n	<li>Attends an event as a representative of Mozilla</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDirections on how to apply for the Certificate of Identification will be emailed to individuals when they are awarded with their Open Badge.\r\n\r\n<strong>Level 3</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Vouching on Mozillians.org</strong>\r\n\r\nBeing vouched on Mozillians.org can be achieved by a Firefox Student Ambassador if they have been awarded the open badge, certificate of identification, and accomplish the following tasks:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Completed all five first program steps as outlined <a href="https://wiki.mozilla.org/StudentAmbassadors/Activities/Startup_Guide">here</a></li>\r\n	<li>Have already set up a non-vouched account on Mozillians.org</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDirections on how to apply to be vouched will be emailed to individuals when they are awarded with their Certificate of Identification.\r\n\r\n<strong>Level 4</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Recommendation to the ReMo program</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you are a Student Ambassador who meets the criteria below and is interested in joining the Mozilla Reps program, we would strongly encourage you to find out more information about the program on the Reps'' <a href="https://reps.mozilla.org/faq/">website</a>. Please note that you will only be recommended to apply for the ReMo program once you have achieved the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Have completed Levels 1-3 in the Student Ambassador program</li>\r\n	<li>Hold a leadership position within their Firefox Club</li>\r\n	<li>Have been a member of the Firefox Student Ambassador program for at least ten months</li>\r\n	<li>Have been vouched by a total of 3 Reps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDirections on how to secure a recommendation will be emailed to individuals when they are vouched on Mozillians.org.\r\n\r\n<strong>Certificate of Appreciation</strong>\r\n\r\nCertificates of Appreciation are available to the following groups:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Regional Marketing Ambassadors who have been in there position for at least 6 months</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese certificates will awarded directly to the Regional Marketing Ambassadors.\r\n\r\n<strong>Rewards</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Very Splendid Gear Package</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease see <a href="https://wiki.mozilla.org/GearStore/Gearavailable#Splendidest_Gear">here</a> for the contents and picture of a Very Splendid Gear Package.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>App Chosen as ''App of the Month''</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Firefox T-shirt for your Club</strong>\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Most downloads via Firefox Club affiliate button (over a one-month period)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Please note that we can only send a maximum of 10 t-shirts to each Club. In addition, special smaller prizes will be awarded each month to those Firefox Clubs in India and Indonesia that achieve the highest number of clicks on their affiliate buttons</b>\r\n\r\n<strong>Firefox Club Gear Welcome Pack</strong>\r\n\r\nIf your Firefox Club has completed all five of the first steps that have been outlined <a href="https://wiki.mozilla.org/StudentAmbassadors/Activities/Startup_Guide#Firefox_Clubs">here</a>.\r\n\r\nPlease note that we will not start to send Welcome Packs until January 2014, but more information about how to qualify and request a Welcome Pack will be placed here shortly.\r\n\r\n$250 USD stipend for an end of year party, highlighted in monthly newsletter, sent a certificate of accomplishment  from Mozilla CMO\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>December 1, 2013: Firefox Club with the largest number of downloads via their affiliates button over the past six months</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>A Note about Gear</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease note that Mozilla gear will not be distributed unless it aligns with one of the situations aligned above or for an event/activity in which we specifically say that we will be providing gear and budget.\r\n\r\nFor any event that we are providing gear and/or budget, we will ask that you request the items from a Rep in your region, who will process the order on your behalf. <b>Kindly do not contact a Rep for gear or budget unless you have been given prior guidance to do so.</b>\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions about when it is appropriate to request gear or budget, please email firefoxstudents[at]mozilla[dot]com. Thanks!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Blog', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-08 03:57:19', '2013-11-08 03:57:19', '', 9, 'http://neekes.com.np/home', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
